"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The trio\", \"from\": 91, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"Ros Canter\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 143}, {\"ngram\": \"4.7 points\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 168}, {\"ngram\": \"the dressage and cross-country phases\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 212}, {\"ngram\": \"their advantage\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 244}, {\"ngram\": \"Canter\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"15 jumping penalties\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 307}, {\"ngram\": \"the latter event\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 327}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the team held their nerve in Ch\\u00e2teau de Versailles as Britain sealed back-to-backOlympicsteam titles for the first time since 1972.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ch\\u00e2teau de Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}, {\"begin\": 388, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7342895207998745, \"rank\": 0.36185883577031014, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 342}, {\"ngram\": \"their nerve\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 359}, {\"ngram\": \"backOlympicsteam\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 427}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Canter who went first for Team GB, knocking down one fence in her round and avoiding any time penalties to extend the overall lead.\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 507, \"title\": \"http://d